{% extends 'ErpSiteBundle::base.html.twig' %}

{% set metaTitle = 'Faq | Zoobdoo' %}
{% set metaDescription = 'Zoobdoo is where proparty managers and tenants connect. Manage all of your properties, post vacant spaces, and receive rent payments online. Sign up today!' %}

{% block pageContent %}

    <main id="main">
        <section class="block-faq">
            <div class="container">
                <h1>FAQ</h1>
                <ul class="accordion">
                    <li>
                        <a class="opener" href="#">What is Zoobdoo? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></a>
                        <div class="slide js-acc-hidden">
                            <p>Zoobdoo is an online property management solution that provides property managers all the tools necessary to effectively and efficiently manage their properties. No matter how many properties you manage, from just a few to as many as you have, we are scalable and provide solutions that will make managing properties a simpler process. We are here to help build your business by keeping things simple and affordable. <a href="#" class="link">Accept rent payments online</a>, pay landlords, get <a href="#" class="link">background and credit checks</a>, send rental applications and collect fees, create rental contracts with online e-signatures, manage your assets, generate tax forms, send notifications and alerts to your tenants by text and email, and much more. All from our secure site. </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a class="opener" href="#">How do the transactions occur? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></a>
                        <div class="slide js-acc-hidden">
                            <p>
                            The tenant submits payment through Zoobdoo tenant portal, payment processes through the Automatic Clearing House (ACH) or Credit Processor (CC), and payment is deposited directly in property managers account.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a class="opener" href="#">Price: How much does it cost? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></a>
                        <div class="slide js-acc-hidden">
                            <p>
                                Property Managers pay a low fee of just $99 for the first property per year, $20 per additional property up to thirty then just $10 per additional property! No contracts or obligations! 
                                Tenant does not pay a fee for ACH transactions. Tenant pays a 2.5% per Credit Card transaction. (Accept Visa, Mastercard and Discover)                   
                                Zoobdoo does not charge an application fee per applicant submission, but you may want to and we can help you do that.
                                Credit, background, and eviction check, just $15 per person.
                                Everything else is included in our low annual fee.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a class="opener" href="#">Do I have to sign a contract? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></a>
                        <div class="slide js-acc-hidden">
                            <p>
                                No, there is no long or short-term contract or obligation. You can cancel at any time.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a class="opener" href="#">Are there any hidden fees or obligations? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></a>
                        <div class="slide js-acc-hidden">
                            <p>There are no hidden fees. No contracts or obligations.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a class="opener" href="#">How do I start accepting tenant payments directly <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></a>
